Hobart Street, east side, just south of 30th Avenue, viewing north toward the latter and showing an old farmhouse and farm. It was owned by the Banta Family from 1873 to 1909. Hobart Street, here, is the former Old Bowery Road which marked the boundary between the towns of Newtown and Long Island City.

Hobart Street (foreground), at the S.E. corner of Thirtieth Ave., showing the Purdy homestead, the property of the heirs of Cornelius Purdy in 1852. One Nancy Banta was the owner from 1891 to 1909. This house was erected prior to the Revolutionary War and was still standing in 1927.

Arthur White.
